The paper discusses the design and implementation of a structured P2P overlay network that provides secure and private communication in NAT-constrained environments. The paper covers topics such as distributed data stores, NAT traversal, and security frameworks utilizing groups and a web-based user interface. These topics are relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Networked Systems (cs.NI), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on networked systems and distributed computing, cs.NI and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories.
